hopobject.body: How many would you like? www.villagepharmacy.com Writing from Nokia World in Abu Dhabi, Microsoft corporate VP of communications Frank Shaw clearly had let the heat get to his temper, saying, "Apple announced yesterday that they were dropping their fees on their 'iWork' suite of apps. Now, since iWork has never gotten much traction, and was already priced like an afterthought, it's hardly that surprising or significant a move."
